Case by case Threshold on short/float is about five percent. $NFLX short interest is nearly 3.5x avg daily volume, non starters for me.

A core tenet of mine regarding short selling is to avoid all stocks with high short interest relative to float and avg daily trading volume. It is a no short dictum that has saved me alot of $. $TSLA is one of those that will never short because of that.
